examples.text: Masayı biraz daha geriye mi çeksek?
examples.translation: Should we move the table back a little more?

glosses: to suck in, pull in, draw in

examples.text: Gözümüzdeki çubuk ve koni hücreleri ışığı kendilerine çekerler.
examples.translation: The rod and cone cells in our eyes absorb the light.

glosses: to bear, endure, put up with, suffer, brook, undergo
to take (a photograph), to shoot (a film, a video)

examples.text: Arkadaşım Yoroz Tepesi'nde ailecek fotoğrafımızı çekti.
examples.translation: My friend took our family photo on Yoroz Hill.

glosses: to draw a lot at random
to weigh, have a weight of

examples.text: Of, telefon buradan niye çekmiyor ya?
examples.translation: Ugh, why can't I get a signal on my phone here?

etymology:
Inherited from Ottoman Turkish چكمك (çekmek, “to pull, drag, draw, attract, imbibe, absorb, weigh, bear, suffer”), from Proto-Turkic *ček-.
Cognates
Cognate with Karakhanid [script needed] (çekmēk, “to draw”), Azerbaijani çəkmək (“to smoke”), Chagatai [script needed] (çekmek, “to pull”), Kipchak [script needed] (çek-, “to pull”), Kyrgyz чегүү (cegüü, “to pull, undergo”), Turkmen çekmek (“to pull, draw”), Uyghur چەكمەك (chekmek, “to undergo”), Uzbek chekmoq (“to pull”).
